</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="76D60DA2FFCBFFF5918228E4FE6BF993" pageId="5" pageNumber="481" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3E735E29FFCBFFF5918228E4FE6BF993" blockId="5.[151,756,1421,1637]" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis id="0CB8823BFFCBFFF5918228E4FEDEFA53" bold="true" box="[151,272,1421,1445]" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
The forewing with pale yellow ground colour flushed with pink grey and the brown hindwing with yellow, pink and grey suffusion distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="F9CC25AAFFCBFFF591822884FEDFF9F3" authorityName="Bassi" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,273,1517,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Afrocharltona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="katanga">
<emphasis id="0CB8823BFFCBFFF591822884FEDFF9F3" box="[151,273,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">A. katanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="F9CC25AAFFCBFFF590482884FDC1F9F3" authorityName="Bassi" authorityYear="2021" box="[349,527,1517,1541]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Afrocharltona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongissima">
<emphasis id="0CB8823BFFCBFFF590482884FDC1F9F3" box="[349,527,1517,1541]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">A. oblongissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male genitalia are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="F9CC25AAFFCBFFF5909D2B64FDFAF9D3" authorityName="Bassi" authorityYear="2021" box="[392,564,1549,1573]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Afrocharltona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="481" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongissima">
<emphasis id="0CB8823BFFCBFFF5909D2B64FDFAF9D3" box="[392,564,1549,1573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">A. oblongissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the valva and apex of the costal arm are shorter and the phallus has two cornuti in the vesica.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="76D60DA2FFCBFFF591822B15FC31FD8F" pageId="5" pageNumber="481" type="description">
<paragraph id="3E735E29FFCBFFF591822B15FE8CF7E2" blockId="5.[151,757,1660,2068]" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">
<emphasis id="0CB8823BFFCBFFF591822B15FED5F962" bold="true" box="[151,283,1660,1684]" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">Description</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="A6F742ACFFCBFFF5903B2B15FEBCF962" box="[302,370,1660,1684]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1894,1916]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,263,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-4@2.[151,1436,257,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Habiti. (1) Afroromieuxia bernardlandryi, holotype. (2) A. bernardlandryi, female paratype. (3) A. aarviki, holotype. (4) A. ustjuzhanini, holotype.(5) Ancylolomia prepiella, male, Lesotho. (6) Diploschistis stygiocrena, male, DRC. (7) Afrocharltona oblongissima, holotype. (8) A. katanga, holotype. Scale bars = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5640162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5640162/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
): Wingspan 
<quantity id="F934F3CCFFCBFFF593152B15FD9CF962" box="[512,594,1660,1684]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="481" unit="mm" value="36.0">36 mm</quantity>
. Labial palpus 2.5 x eye diameter, chestnut brown, apically paler. Maxillary palpus basally chestnut brown, apically paler. Antenna thickened, brown with costa paler. Frons rounded, slightly produced, off-white. Vertex and patagia pale yellow. Tegulae and thorax pale yellow, sprinkled with brown. Forewing and hindwing as in 
<figureCitation id="A6F742ACFFCBFFF591822A35FF15F882" box="[151,219,1884,1908]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1894,1916]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,263,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-4@2.[151,1436,257,1845]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Habiti. (1) Afroromieuxia bernardlandryi, holotype. (2) A. bernardlandryi, female paratype. (3) A. aarviki, holotype. (4) A. ustjuzhanini, holotype.(5) Ancylolomia prepiella, male, Lesotho. (6) Diploschistis stygiocrena, male, DRC. (7) Afrocharltona oblongissima, holotype. (8) A. katanga, holotype. Scale bars = 10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5640162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5640162/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
. Forewing sprinkled with brown, more intensely basally; suboval brown dot after cell; fringes bright ivory yellow. Underside pale yellow, suffused with brown dorsally in hindwing. Abdomen pale yellow. Legs yellow; tibial spurs asymmetrical, first pair longer than apical pair.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E735E29FFCBFFF5922A2C68FAB3FDAF" blockId="5.[831,1437,257,633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">
Male genitalia. (
<figureCitation id="A6F742ACFFCBFFF592E92C68FB9CFEEF" box="[1020,1106,257,281]" captionStart="Figs 9-15" captionStartId="4.[151,192,1722,1744]" captionTargetBox="[151,1407,257,1660]" captionTargetId="figure-4@4.[151,1436,257,1725]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 9-15. Habitat and male genitalia. (9) Habitat of Afrocharltona oblongissima (photo G. Bassi, Dec., 2010). (10) A. oblongissima, holotype. (11) A. oblongissima, paratype, Botswana, Maun, uncus and gnathos in lateral view. (12) Afroromieuxia bernardlandryi, holotype. (13) Afrocharltona katanga, holotype. (14) Afroromieuxia bernardlandryi, paratype, uncus, gnathos and costal process in lateral view. (15) Diploschistis stygiocrena, DRC." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5640166" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5640166/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Uncus as long as gnathos, strongly bulged dorsally and with apex blunt and notched. Gnathos with pointed and slightly upcurved apex. Tegumen almost twice as long as uncus, narrow. Vinculum stout, subtriangular. Pseudosaccus narrow, concave. Juxta suboval, with subtriangular protrusions medioventrally. Valva extremely elongated, narrowing apically, with rounded cucullus; costal arm slightly longer than valva, strongly sclerotized, with apical pointed thorn. Phallus with bent phallobase: vesica with two light sclerotized cornuti and minute scobinations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3E735E29FFCBFFF5922A2F08FC31FD8F" blockId="5.[831,1437,257,633]" box="[831,1023,609,633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="481">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
